General composition I is the subject to develop the sense of composition, visual thinking and observation skills to create conditions for the formation of individual mode of expression. The course includes following topics:
rhythm; focus; dynamics; symmetry; contrast; the differences between two and three dimensional rooms; relations of location, proportion and color.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course developes observation skills, visual thinking and the sense of composition .Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion a student understands the core of visual composition and is familiar to various categories of compositon and is able to analyze it. The student is able to think visually, can also provide a comprehensive and visually convincing format for his/her work.
